[{"name":"Traveler's Guide to the Sword Coast","author":"Unknown","written":"1480 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A practical wayfarer's companion aimed at merchants and pilgrims rather than scholars — mile markers, toll customs, and which inns will actually honour a prepaid room.\n\nThe author advises that the Coast's main caravan routes are profitable precisely because they are dangerous, and that hiring armed escort is cheaper than recovering stolen wagons.","tags":["sword_coast","travel","trade"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/2/21/Book_bg3.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/376?cb=20210717021405","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Traveler%27s_Guide_to_the_Sword_Coast"},{"name":"The Dessarin River","author":"Unknown","written":"1470 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A river trader's handbook describing the Dessarin from its headwaters in the Evermoors to the trade towns where barges turn goods toward Waterdeep and the Inner Sea.\n\nChapters cover seasonal floods, toll rights at ford towns, and which stretches are safe only when the Zhent patrols are paid and smiling.","tags":["dessarin","trade","geography"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Dessarin_River"},{"name":"Trail Tales of the North","author":"Jhalivar Thrunn","written":"1197 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Jhalivar Thrunn collected first-person accounts from trappers, scouts, and refugees who crossed the Evermoors and lived — though not always intact — to tell of it.\n\nThe earliest edition at Candlekeep bears water stains and a note that two tales were added in a hand Thrunn disowned; readers still argue which stories he wished to suppress.","tags":["north","adventure","travel"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Trail_Tales_of_the_North"},{"name":"The North: Guide to the Savage Frontier","author":"Various sages of the North","written":"1358 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A comprehensive gazetteer produced by a council of sages — less colourful than Volo, more exhaustive on geography, demographics, and the political balance between Luskan, Neverwinter, and the dwarf holds.\n\nBoxed sets of maps once accompanied the text; surviving copies without maps still command high prices at Candlekeep.","tags":["north","geography","history"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://d1vzi28wh99zvq.cloudfront.net/images/44/17543-thumb140.jpg","content_link":"https://www.dmsguild.com/product/17543/The-North-Guide-to-the-Savage-Frontier-2e"},{"name":"The Book of the Coast","author":"Mespert of Baldur's Gate","written":"1293 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Mespert of Baldur's Gate assembled merchant contracts, harbour tariffs, and pirate amnesty proclamations into a single reference for factors sailing the Sword Coast trade.\n\nThe binding is utilitarian; margins swarm with later hands noting which clauses Lords' Alliance courts actually enforce.","tags":["sword_coast","trade","law"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Book_of_the_Coast"},{"name":"The City of Neverwinter","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1372 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"An anonymous survey of Neverwinter's wards, noble houses, and the Mount Hotenow shadow that hangs over civic pride — written before the city's latest rebuilding.\n\nReaders comparing editions can trace disaster after disaster in the crossed-out street maps and hastily pasted addenda.","tags":["neverwinter","geography","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_City_of_Neverwinter"},{"name":"Travels Along the Sword Coast","author":"Elminster of Shadowdale","written":"1357 DR","rarity":"very rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Elminster's earlier coastal diary — less sermon, more notebook — records inns where mages pay in secrets, pirates who honour guest-right, and the small customs that keep trade flowing when law fails.\n\nThe sage claims he never intended publication; the ink stains suggest otherwise.","tags":["sword_coast","history","travel"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Travels_Along_the_Sword_Coast"},{"name":"The Mysterious Harpers","author":"Alamar Djelmuth","written":"before 1369 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Alamar Djelmuth's speculative history treats the Harpers as legend, conspiracy, and occasional nuisance — compiling rumours from taverns between Neverwinter and Amn.\n\nHarper agents reportedly bought and burned the first printing; surviving copies are prized by collectors who may not survive owning one.","tags":["harpers","history","intrigue"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Mysterious_Harpers"},{"name":"The Neverwinter Wood","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1372 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A naturalist's account of the forest east of Neverwinter — fey crossings, owlbear dens, and the Uthgardt taboos that forbid certain paths even in pursuit of game.\n\nThe author vanished mid-manuscript; the last pages describe lights that answered when called by name.","tags":["neverwinter","nature","myth"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Neverwinter_Wood_(book)"},{"name":"The Sharp Eye and Sharper Tongue: Observations of a Learned Sage","author":"Ammathair Hawkfeather, Sage of Waterdeep","written":"1359 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Ammathair Hawkfeather of Waterdeep documents civic absurdities — guild pride, noble feuds, and the arcane accidents that result when apprentices show off for crowds.\n\nThe tone is satirical but the facts check out; several subjects attempted to buy every copy and succeeded only in raising the price.","tags":["waterdeep","history","philosophy"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Sharp_Eye_and_Sharper_Tongue:_Observations_of_a_Learned_Sage"},{"name":"Tathaero's Short Sword Coast Chronicle","author":"Aldreth Tathaero, Scribe for Hire of Athkatla","written":"1487 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Aldreth Tathaero, scribe for hire, compiled a decade of coastal news — pirate captures, noble marriages, temple schisms, and one suspiciously detailed account of a red dragon over Triboar.\n\nTathaero disclaimers that accuracy follows payment; historians still cite the chronicle when better sources are silent.","tags":["sword_coast","history","trade"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Tathaero%27s_Short_Sword_Coast_Chronicle"},{"name":"Trade Way Travel Stops","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1372 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Trade Way Travel Stops — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to before 1372 DR.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["travel","trade","sword_coast"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Trade_Way_Travel_Stops"},{"name":"The Trade of Blades","author":"Augustavus Cale","written":"before 1372 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Trade of Blades — Commercial wisdom dressed as prose — prices, routes, guild customs, and when to walk away from a deal. Augustavus Cale is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to before 1372 DR.\n\nFactors along the Long Road keep folded excerpts in strongboxes next to their scales and seals.","tags":["neverwinter","trade","war"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Trade_of_Blades"},{"name":"Tales Told by the Warm Fireside","author":"Korin of Neverwinter","written":"1334 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Tales Told by the Warm Fireside — A popular tale in print — performed in taverns before it was ever bound between covers. Korin of Neverwinter is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1334 DR.\n\nCritics call it low art; innkeepers call it excellent for business on rainy nights.","tags":["neverwinter","fiction","culture"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Tales_Told_by_the_Warm_Fireside"},{"name":"The Rise of Randral","author":"Sandreth Yendrel of Neverwinter","written":"1326 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Rise of Randral — A popular tale in print — performed in taverns before it was ever bound between covers. Sandreth Yendrel of Neverwinter is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1326 DR.\n\nCritics call it low art; innkeepers call it excellent for business on rainy nights.","tags":["neverwinter","fiction","adventure"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Rise_of_Randral"},{"name":"Tavern Dancing My Way to Wizardly Might","author":"Jerenneth Ghaluin of Neverwinter","written":"1349 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Tavern Dancing My Way to Wizardly Might — A treatise on magic as it is actually practiced — wards, reputations, and the price of mispronunciation. Jerenneth Ghaluin of Neverwinter is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1349 DR.\n\nComplete copies are rare; excerpted versions circulate among mages who insist the missing pages do not matter.","tags":["neverwinter","arcane","fiction"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Tavern_Dancing_My_Way_to_Wizardly_Might"},{"name":"Translations from Kara-Tur Haiku","author":"Lhaeo of Shadowdale","written":"1354 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Translations from Kara-Tur Haiku — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Lhaeo of Shadowdale is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1354 DR.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["philosophy","culture","travel"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Translations_from_Kara-Tur_Haiku"},{"name":"The High History of Faerûnian Archmages Mighty","author":"Antarn the Sage","written":"1366 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The High History of Faerûnian Archmages Mighty — A treatise on magic as it is actually practiced — wards, reputations, and the price of mispronunciation. Antarn the Sage is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1366 DR.\n\nComplete copies are rare; excerpted versions circulate among mages who insist the missing pages do not matter.","tags":["arcane","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_High_History_of_Faerûnian_Archmages_Mighty"},{"name":"The History of the Moonsea North","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1479 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The History of the Moonsea North — A chronicle preserved in northern and coastal scriptoria — dates, names, and the sort of detail merchants pretend not to need. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to before 1479 DR.\n\nLater hands added marginal dates and crossed out names; historians still argue which revisions were propaganda.","tags":["north","history","moonsea"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_History_of_the_Moonsea_North"},{"name":"Traveler's Guide to Icewind Dale","author":"Unknown","written":"1281–1312 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Traveler's Guide to Icewind Dale — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to 1281–1312 DR.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["north","travel","geography"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/d/de/IWD2_white_book.png/revision/latest?cb=20221115133446","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Traveler%27s_Guide_to_Icewind_Dale"},{"name":"Traveler's Guide to Silverymoon – Inns, Taverns, and Local Law","author":"Imgath Gland and Sagreth Kormun","written":"before 1370 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Traveler's Guide to Silverymoon – Inns, Taverns, and Local Law — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Imgath Gland and Sagreth Kormun is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to before 1370 DR.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["north","travel","law"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Traveler%27s_Guide_to_Silverymoon_–_Inns,_Taverns,_and_Local_Law"},{"name":"To Harp and to Help","author":"Alustriel","written":"1271 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"To Harp and to Help — Harper-related lore — coded, partial, and dangerous to quote without looking over your shoulder. Alustriel is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1271 DR.\n\nNon-Harper readers report the prose is readable; Harper readers report it is a test.","tags":["harpers","philosophy","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/To_Harp_and_to_Help"},{"name":"To Harp and Help—An Addendum","author":"Alustriel","written":"1294 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"To Harp and Help—An Addendum — Harper-related lore — coded, partial, and dangerous to quote without looking over your shoulder. Alustriel is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1294 DR.\n\nNon-Harper readers report the prose is readable; Harper readers report it is a test.","tags":["harpers","philosophy","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/To_Harp_and_Help—An_Addendum"},{"name":"The Song of One Harp","author":"Storm Silverhand","written":"1302 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Song of One Harp — Harper-related lore — coded, partial, and dangerous to quote without looking over your shoulder. Storm Silverhand is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1302 DR.\n\nNon-Harper readers report the prose is readable; Harper readers report it is a test.","tags":["harpers","music","arcane"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Song_of_One_Harp"},{"name":"The Guild: Hidden Rulers of Baldur's Gate","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1492 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Guild: Hidden Rulers of Baldur's Gate — A text that names names — or appears to — and has outlived more than one owner. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to before 1492 DR.\n\nSeveral entries end mid-sentence, as if the author learned something and chose discretion over royalties.","tags":["baldurs_gate","intrigue","trade"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Guild%3A_Hidden_Rulers_of_Baldur%27s_Gate"},{"name":"The Compleat Dragon-Hunter","author":"Smerdiuk Dragonbane of Arabel","written":"1300 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Compleat Dragon-Hunter — Military history and counsel from campaigns fought along the Frontier and the Sword Coast. Smerdiuk Dragonbane of Arabel is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1300 DR.\n\nVeterans annotate the margins with corrections; green officers treat those notes as insults until the first ambush.","tags":["war","monsters","nature"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/c/c9/Grim_Bounty.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/400?cb=20211125131444","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Compleat_Dragon-Hunter"},{"name":"Treatise on Monsters Known and Unknown","author":"Thardon Ilvynner","written":"516–522 DR","rarity":"ancient","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Treatise on Monsters Known and Unknown — Natural history from hunters, riverfolk, and sages who went outside and wrote down what bit them. Thardon Ilvynner is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 516–522 DR.\n\nSeasonal addenda in surviving copies suggest the author revised the work every year they lived to see spring.","tags":["nature","monsters","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Treatise_on_Monsters_Known_and_Unknown"},{"name":"The Origin Myths—A Treatise","author":"Dunkelzahn of Candlekeep","written":"1354 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Origin Myths—A Treatise — Legends collected from tavern verse, elder memory, and sources no scholar will swear to in court. Dunkelzahn of Candlekeep is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1354 DR.\n\nEach generation adds a verse; purists claim the oldest layer is true and everything since is flattery.","tags":["myth","religion","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Origin_Myths—A_Treatise"},{"name":"The Field of Battle","author":"Hludar Sylem","written":"before 1369 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Field of Battle — Military history and counsel from campaigns fought along the Frontier and the Sword Coast. Hludar Sylem is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to before 1369 DR.\n\nVeterans annotate the margins with corrections; green officers treat those notes as insults until the first ambush.","tags":["war","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Field_of_Battle"},{"name":"Things a Knight Should Know","author":"Myrintar Hasantar","written":"1307 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Things a Knight Should Know — Military history and counsel from campaigns fought along the Frontier and the Sword Coast. Myrintar Hasantar is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1307 DR.\n\nVeterans annotate the margins with corrections; green officers treat those notes as insults until the first ambush.","tags":["war","philosophy","culture"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Things_a_Knight_Should_Know"},{"name":"Teachings of the Morning's Glory","author":"Thorndar Erlin","written":"20 DR","rarity":"ancient","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Teachings of the Morning's Glory — Devotional and doctrinal writing circulated among temples and faithful households along the trade routes. Thorndar Erlin is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 20 DR.\n\nTemple libraries hold the cleanest editions; roadside chapbooks may omit verses the clergy prefer not to recite aloud.","tags":["religion","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Teachings_of_the_Morning%27s_Glory"},{"name":"The Healing Power of Prayer: Curative Rituals of the House of Ilmater","author":"Unknown","written":"unknown","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Healing Power of Prayer: Curative Rituals of the House of Ilmater — Devotional and doctrinal writing circulated among temples and faithful households along the trade routes. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to unknown.\n\nTemple libraries hold the cleanest editions; roadside chapbooks may omit verses the clergy prefer not to recite aloud.","tags":["religion","philosophy"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Healing_Power_of_Prayer%3A_Curative_Rituals_of_the_House_of_Ilmater"},{"name":"Traagor's Guide to Inns and Taverns","author":"Rooth Traagor and Eldwin Traagor","written":"mid-14th century DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Traagor's Guide to Inns and Taverns — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Rooth Traagor and Eldwin Traagor is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to mid-14th century DR.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["travel","culture","trade"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Traagor%27s_Guide_to_Inns_and_Taverns"},{"name":"Tall Tales: A Ranger's Life","author":"Amhritar the Tall","written":"1326 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Tall Tales: A Ranger's Life — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Amhritar the Tall is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1326 DR.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["travel","adventure","nature"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Tall_Tales%3A_A_Ranger%27s_Life"},{"name":"The Great Diaspora of Netheril","author":"Unknown","written":"after −457 DR","rarity":"ancient","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Great Diaspora of Netheril — A chronicle preserved in northern and coastal scriptoria — dates, names, and the sort of detail merchants pretend not to need. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to after −457 DR.\n\nLater hands added marginal dates and crossed out names; historians still argue which revisions were propaganda.","tags":["history","arcane"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Great_Diaspora_of_Netheril"},{"name":"The Tome of the Dragon","author":"Sammaster","written":"905 DR","rarity":"legendary","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Tome of the Dragon — A treatise on magic as it is actually practiced — wards, reputations, and the price of mispronunciation. Sammaster is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 905 DR.\n\nComplete copies are rare; excerpted versions circulate among mages who insist the missing pages do not matter.","tags":["arcane","monsters","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Tome_of_the_Dragon"},{"name":"Testament of Jade","author":"Dennison the Jade","written":"before 714 DR","rarity":"ancient","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Testament of Jade — A chronicle preserved in northern and coastal scriptoria — dates, names, and the sort of detail merchants pretend not to need. Dennison the Jade is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to before 714 DR.\n\nLater hands added marginal dates and crossed out names; historians still argue which revisions were propaganda.","tags":["elves","history","arcane"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/7/77/Testament_of_jade.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/400?cb=20201117145548","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Testament_of_Jade"},{"name":"The Glory of the Dragon","author":"Danchas the Scribe","written":"before 1371 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Glory of the Dragon — Legends collected from tavern verse, elder memory, and sources no scholar will swear to in court. Danchas the Scribe is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to before 1371 DR.\n\nEach generation adds a verse; purists claim the oldest layer is true and everything since is flattery.","tags":["monsters","myth","culture"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Glory_of_the_Dragon"},{"name":"The Steel Princess' Field Guide to Tactics of the Purple Dragon","author":"Princess Alusair Obarskyr","written":"1364 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Steel Princess' Field Guide to Tactics of the Purple Dragon — Military history and counsel from campaigns fought along the Frontier and the Sword Coast. Princess Alusair Obarskyr is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1364 DR.\n\nVeterans annotate the margins with corrections; green officers treat those notes as insults until the first ambush.","tags":["war","history","cormyr"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Steel_Princess%27_Field_Guide_to_Tactics_of_the_Purple_Dragon"},{"name":"The Obarskyr Family Histories","author":"Various court scribes","written":"1308 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Obarskyr Family Histories — A chronicle preserved in northern and coastal scriptoria — dates, names, and the sort of detail merchants pretend not to need. Various court scribes is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1308 DR.\n\nLater hands added marginal dates and crossed out names; historians still argue which revisions were propaganda.","tags":["cormyr","history","politics"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Obarskyr_Family_Histories"},{"name":"The Bhaalspawn Saga","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1492 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Bhaalspawn Saga — A popular tale in print — performed in taverns before it was ever bound between covers. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to before 1492 DR.\n\nCritics call it low art; innkeepers call it excellent for business on rainy nights.","tags":["fiction","history","myth"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/2/2d/Open_book_bg3.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/400?cb=20230929065410","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Bhaalspawn_Saga"},{"name":"The True Life of Cyric","author":"Rinda","written":"before 1368 DR","rarity":"very rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The True Life of Cyric — A chronicle preserved in northern and coastal scriptoria — dates, names, and the sort of detail merchants pretend not to need. Rinda is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to before 1368 DR.\n\nLater hands added marginal dates and crossed out names; historians still argue which revisions were propaganda.","tags":["history","religion","intrigue"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_True_Life_of_Cyric"},{"name":"The Poet's Song","author":"The blind poet of Daargard Keep","written":"centuries before 1372 DR","rarity":"ancient","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Poet's Song — Legends collected from tavern verse, elder memory, and sources no scholar will swear to in court. The blind poet of Daargard Keep is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to centuries before 1372 DR.\n\nEach generation adds a verse; purists claim the oldest layer is true and everything since is flattery.","tags":["myth","poetry","history"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/6/69/The_Poet%27s_Song.png/revision/latest?cb=20210712212146","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Poet%27s_Song"},{"name":"The Northern Four Adventuring Troupe","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1372 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"The Northern Four Adventuring Troupe — A popular tale in print — performed in taverns before it was ever bound between covers. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to before 1372 DR.\n\nCritics call it low art; innkeepers call it excellent for business on rainy nights.","tags":["fiction","adventure","north"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/The_Northern_Four_Adventuring_Troupe"}]